NEXUS: "Engineer, to truly understand our network topology, you must understand
       bridge networks - the virtual switches that connect containers. Docker
       creates these bridges, and each one forms an isolated network segment.
       Let me show you how they work from both inside and outside the containers."

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

OBJECTIVE
═════════
A bridge network is like a virtual network switch. Containers on the same
bridge can communicate; containers on different bridges cannot (by default).

Docker provides:
  - Default bridge: Basic connectivity, NO automatic DNS
  - User-defined bridges: Better isolation, automatic DNS between containers

Our station uses user-defined bridges (frontend_net, backend_net) for
controlled communication.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

TASKS
═════

NOTE: These tasks should be run from the Docker HOST, not inside a container.

[ ] Task 1: List All Docker Networks
    Command: docker network ls
    Find: bridge (default), network-lab_frontend_net, network-lab_backend_net

[ ] Task 2: Inspect Frontend Network
    Command: docker network inspect network-lab_frontend_net
    Find the subnet (172.20.0.0/24), gateway (172.20.0.1), and connected containers.

[ ] Task 3: Compare Default vs User-Defined Bridge
    # Default bridge has NO DNS:
    docker run -d --name test1 nginx:alpine
    docker exec test1 ping -c 1 client  # FAILS - no DNS
    docker rm -f test1

    # User-defined bridge has DNS:
    docker exec client ping -c 1 server  # WORKS

[ ] Task 4: View Bridge from Inside Container
    Command: docker exec -it client bash
    Inside: ip addr                    # See eth0 interface
    Inside: ip route                   # See gateway (172.20.0.1)
    Inside: exit

[ ] Task 5: List Containers on a Network
    Command: docker network inspect network-lab_frontend_net \
      --format '{{range .Containers}}{{.Name}}: {{.IPv4Address}}{{"\n"}}{{end}}'

[ ] Task 6: Show Container's Networks
    Command: docker inspect client \
      --format '{{range $net, $config := .NetworkSettings.Networks}}{{$net}}: {{$config.IPAddress}}{{"\n"}}{{end}}'

[ ] Task 7: Verify DNS on User-Defined Bridge
    Command: docker exec client nslookup server
    Command: docker exec client nslookup api
    Automatic DNS resolution between containers!

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

